headline: US needs 'unified approach' on AI companies competing with China
summary: American AI executives are speaking before lawmakers on Capitol Hill on Thursday about how the US can keep a competitive advantage against China. Among the CEOs include OpenAI CEO Sam Altman and Advanced Micro Devices (AMD) CEO Lisa Su. Chamber of Progress Founder and CEO Adam Kovacevich comes on Catalysts to speak more about how the second Trump administration's Federal Trade Commission (FTC) is approaching antitrust cases in Big Tech and the ongoing "AI arms race" with China. Additionally, Alphabet (GOOG, GOOGL) shares are slowly crawling back in Thursday's trading session after falling off yesterday on headlines that Apple (AAPL) plans to integrate AI search features into its Safari web browser, according to Apple senior vice president of services Eddy Cue's testimony to US Department of Justice (DOJ) officials. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Catalysts here.
